-- Latin American Nations Are ‘Equal Partners,’ Obama Tells Summit
-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 2012-04-14T16:14:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-14/latin-american-nations-are-equal-partners-obama-tells-summit.html
President  Barack Obama  told Latin
American leaders that the U.S. has “never felt more excited
about prospects of working as equal partners with our brothers
and sisters in Latin America and the Caribbean.”  Obama, speaking at the Summit of the Americas in Cartagena,
Colombia, stressed the need for democracy and the rule of law as
elements that pave the way for expanding economies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
